snippet.title: GATE 2025 Topper Shares CS + DA Strategy & What You Need to Know About GATE DA
snippet.description:
In this video, I’m talking to Anurag Tripathi, who secured AIR 85 in GATE CS 2025, AIR 154 in GATE DA 2025, and also AIR 67 in GATE CS 2024!

Anurag Tripathi: https://in.linkedin.com/in/anurag-g-tripathi-1665092bb

We discuss his complete GATE journey, how he managed to crack both GATE CS and GATE DA together.
This conversation also includes a helpful breakdown of GATE DA basics — what GATE DA paper is about, how GATE DA differs from GATE CS, and who should attempt GATE DA.

Whether you're preparing for GATE CS, DA, or both — this interview covers real, practical strategies and mindset tips that can help you stay consistent, avoid common mistakes, and build towards a top rank.

✅ Full GATE CS & DA Preparation Strategy
✅ How to manage GATE with college and coding practice
✅ PYQs, test series, and short notes approach
✅ GATE DA: syllabus overview, overlap with CS, and resource suggestions
✅ Interview preparation tips and post-GATE plans

snippet.title: GATE CS 2026 Roadmap | How to Get Under AIR 100 Starting in July | Month-by-Month Prep Strategy
snippet.description:
In this video, I’m sharing a complete 7-month preparation roadmap for GATE CS 2026 — designed for those starting in July and aiming to secure a top rank to get into top IITS.

Whether you're starting late, juggling college/job, or have attempted GATE before — this guide will help you prepare smartly, avoid common mistakes, and stay consistent till the very end.

This plan is refined from my own experience of cracking GATE and interacting with several top rankers who achieved amazing results even with limited time.
If you're ready to commit fully, this roadmap will give you the clarity and direction you need.

✅ Subject-wise & phase-wise strategy
✅ How to balance revision, PYQs, and test series
✅ How many hours to study and how to track progress
✅ The mindset to stay consistent & not quit halfway
✅ Full breakdown from July to January
